tyle=\"width:9em;\" | Album\n|-\n!<small>[[Gaon Music Chart|KOR]]</small><br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon|title=Gaon Digital Chart|work=Gaon Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|accessdate=April 16, 2020|language=Korean}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"Still\" <small>(\uaca8\uc6b8\uc744 \uac77\ub2e4)</small>\n| 2019\n| \u2014\n| rowspan=\"1\" {{N/A}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" {{N/A|Non-album single}}\n|-\n! colspan=\"6\" |Soundtrack appearances\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | \"After Love\" (Ballad Ver.) {{small|({{lang|ko|\uc0ac\ub791\ud55c \ud6c4\uc5d0 (Ballad Ver.)}})}}\n| 2014\n| \u2014\n| {{N/A}}\n|''Love Cells'' OST Part.2\n|-\n| colspan=\"5\" style=\"font-size:8pt;\" | \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that region.\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[2016 MBC Drama Awards|35th MBC Drama Awards]]\n| rowspan=2|Best New Actor\n| ''Start Again''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[2017 SBS Drama Awards|25th SBS Drama Awards]]\n| ''[[I'm Sorry, But I Love You]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n<!-- Per [[WP:ELMINOFFICIAL]], choose one official website only -->\n* {{twitter|Maboyyyyy}}\n* {{Hancinema person|Park_Sun-ho|Park Sun-ho}}\n* {{IMDb name|7731037|Park Sun-ho}}\n* {{IMDb name|6969263|Park Sun-ho}}\n* [http://movie.naver.com/movie/bi/pi/basic.nhn?code=350908 Park Sun-ho] on [[Naver|Naver Movies]] {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Produce 101}}\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Park, Sun-ho}}\n[[Category:1993 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Produce 101 contestants]]\n[[Category:South Korean male models]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:IHQ artists]]\n\n{{Korea-actor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|South Korean track cyclist|Park Seon-ho}}\n{{Korean name|Park}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Park Sun-ho\n| image           = 190102 \ubc15\uc120\ud638 MBN '\ucd5c\uace0\uc758 \uce58\ud0a8' \uc81c\uc791\ubc1c\ud45c\ud68c \uc9c1\ucea0 02.png\n| image_size      =\n| birth_name      =\n| birth_date      = {{Birth date and age|1993|5|9}}\n| birth_place     = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| occupation      = Actor, model\n| years_active    =\n| education       =\n| agent           = [[SidusHQ]]\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent|\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\ubc15|\uc120\ud638}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u6734|\u5ba3|\u6d69}}\n| rr              = Bak Seon-ho\n| mr              = Pak S\u014fnho\n}}}}\n\n'''Park Sun-ho''' (born May 9, 1993) is a South Korean actor and model. Park made his acting debut in the  [[Korean drama|television series]] ''[[Golden Rainbow (TV series)|Golden Rainbow]]'' (2013). A rising new actor, he has since been cast as one of the lead in ''Love Cells'' (2014), ''Start Again'' (2016) and ''[[I'm Sorry, But I Love You]]'' (2016).<ref>{{cite web|title=[My Name] \ubc15\uc120\ud638 (1)|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/726697|work=10Asia|accessdate=2017-04-20|date=9 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Kim Yoo-jeong, Park Sun-ho, Park Hyeon-woo-I, Choi Young-min donate talent for stray dogs|url=http://www.hancinema.net/kim-yoo-jeong-park-sun-ho-park-hyeon-woo-i-choi-young-min-donate-talent-for-stray-dogs-88933.html|website=[[Hancinema]]|accessdate=2017-04-20|date=27 November 2015}}</ref>\n\nHe was a contestant in Mnet's survival show \"Produce X 101\". He was eliminated during episode 11 at rank 25.\n\n== Filmography ==\n\n=== Television series ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2013 || ''[[Golden Rainbow (TV series)|Golden Rainbow]]'' || Kim Young-won / <br /> Michinski Forever || [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0002730499|script-title=ko:\uc2e0\uc608 \ubc15\uc120\ud638\u00b7\ud5ec\ub85c\ube44\ub108\uc2a4 \uc720\uc544\ub77c, \u2018\ud669\uae08\ubb34\uc9c0\uac1c\u2019 \ud569\ub958|date=8 March 2014|website=Osen|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014 || ''Love Cells'' || Ma Dae-choong || [[Naver]] <br /> TV Cast\n| <ref>{{cite web|title=Jang Hyeok, Kim Woo-bin and Kim Yoo-jeong in ''Love Cells''|url=http://www.hancinema.net/jang-hyeok-kim-woo-bin-and-kim-yoo-jeong-in-love-cells-73419.html|website=[[Hancinema]]|accessdate=2017-04-20|date=16 September 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2015 || ''[[Shine or Go Crazy]]'' || Wang Wi || MBC\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000305725|script-title=ko:\ubc15\uc120\ud638, \u2018\ube5b\ub098\uac70\ub098 \ubbf8\uce58\uac70\ub098\u2019 \ud569\ub958\u2026 \uc7a5\ud601\uacfc \ub450 \ubc88\uc9f8 \uc778\uc5f0|date=12 January 2015|website=Sports Donga|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Rude Miss Young-ae - Season 14'' || Park Sun-ho || [[TVN (South Korea)|tvN]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=382&aid=0000368582|script-title=ko:\u2018\ub9c9\uc601\uc560\u2019, \uc2dc\uc98c14\ub85c \ub3cc\uc544\uc654\ub2e4\u2026 \ub300\ubcf8\ub9ac\ub529 \ud604\uc7a5 \uacf5\uac1c|date=17 June 2015|website=Sports Donga|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2016 || ''Start Again'' || Kang Ji-wook || MBC\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=''Let's Make a New Start'' leading actors Park Min-ji, Woori, Kim Jeong-hoon and Park Sun-ho share snapshot|url=http://www.hancinema.net/-let-s-make-a-new-start-leading-actors-park-min-ji-woori-kim-jeong-hoon-and-park-sun-ho-share-snapshot-94963.html|website=[[Hancinema]]|accessdate=2017-04-20|date=27 May 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[I'm Sorry, But I Love You]]'' || Kang Nam-goo || [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=112&aid=0002871225|title=\ubc15\uc120\ud638X\uae40\ubbfc\uc11c, SBS \uc77c\uc77c\uadf9 '\uc544\uc784\uc3d8\ub9ac \uac15\ub0a8\uad6c' \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5|date=1 December 2016|website=TV Report|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2017 || [[Hospital Ship (TV series)|''Hospital Ship'']] || Kim Jae-hwan || MBC\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=421&aid=0002849143|script-title=ko:\ubc15\uc120\ud638, '\ubcd1\uc6d0\uc120' \ud569\ub958\u2026\ud558\uc9c0\uc6d0 \ud6c4\ubc30 \uc758\uc0ac \ubcc0\uc2e0 [\uacf5\uc2dd]|date=20 July 2017|website=News1|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018 || ''[[A Poem a Day]]'' || Han Joo-yong || tvN\n| <ref>{{cite news|author=Shin, So-won|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=117&aid=0003000310|script-title=ko:[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \"\uc0e4\ubc29\uc0e4\ubc29 \uc120\ud638\uc528\" \ubc15\uc120\ud638, '\uc2dc\ub97c \uc78a\uc740 \uadf8\ub300\uc5d0\uac8c' \ucd9c\uc5f0\ud655\uc815|website=Naver|publisher=My Daily|language=ko|date=2018-01-15|accessdate=2018-04-09}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Best Chicken]]'' || Park Choi-go || [[Maeil Broadcasting Network|MBN]] and Dramax\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/the-best-chicken-tells-of-chicken-and-revenge-124821.html|title=\"The Best Chicken\" Tells of Chicken and Revenge|date=10 December 2018|website=Hancinema|publisher=Newsen}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020 || ''[[Rugal (TV series)|Rugal]]'' || Lee Gwang-cheol || OCN\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/new-drama-rugal-133126.html|title=\"Rugal\" |date= 28 March 2020|website=Hancinema|}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Television shows ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! Ref.\n|-\n|-\n| 2019 || ''[[Produce X 101]]'' || Contestant || [[Mnet (TV channel)|Mnet]]\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://produce-x-101.mnet.com/profile/66|title=\ubc15\uc120\ud638 ( sidusHQ ) {{!}} PRODUCE X 101 [\uc5e0\ub137\ub2f7\ucef4]|website=produce-x-101.mnet.com|language=ko|access-date=2019-04-27}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Film ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:500px\"\n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2014 || ''[[Mourning Grave]]'' || Pin-up male student 1\