{"title_page": "Vitaly Zdorovetskiy", "text_new": "{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = Vitaly Zdorovetskiy\n| image           = Vitaly Zdorovetskiy, April 2020.jpg\n| caption         = Zdorovetskiy in April 2020\n| channel_name    = VitalyzdTv\n| views           = 1.69+ billion\n| view_date =January 24, 2020\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1992|03|08}}\n| birth_place     = [[Murmansk]], [[Murmansk Oblast]], [[Russian Federation]]\n| origin          = [[Boca Raton, Florida]], United States| Current Residence         = [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n| nationality     = Russian \n| alma_mater      = Boca Raton Community High School\n| occupation      = YouTube personality, actor, businessman\n| website         = \n| pseudonym       = \n| years_active    = 2011\u2013present\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Practical joke|Pranking]]\n* [[comedy]]\n}}\n| subscribers     = 10.3+ million \n| subscriber_date = January 9, 2020\n| network         = [[Disney Digital Network|Maker]] (2011\u20132014)<br />[[Collective Digital Studio|Collective Digital]] (2014\u2013present)\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Roman Atwood]]\n* [[Dennis Roady]]\n* [[Yousef Erakat]]\n* [[Protosun Productions]]\n* [[Nelk Boys]]\n* [[Logan Paul]]\n}}\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2012\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2013\n| diamond_button     = yes\n| diamond_year       = 2019\n| stats_update    = November 19, 2019\n}}\n\n'''Vitaly Zdorovetskiy''' ({{IPAc-en|v|\u026a|\u02c8|t|\u00e6|l|i|_|z|\u0259|\u02cc|d|\u0252r|\u0259|\u02c8|v|j|\u025b|t|s|k|i}} {{respell|vih|TAL|ee|_|z\u0259|DORR|\u0259|VYET|skee}}; {{lang-rus|link=no|\u0412\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0301\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0301\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439|p=v\u02b2\u026a\u02c8tal\u02b2\u026aj zd\u0259r\u0250\u02c8v\u02b2\u025btsk\u02b2\u026aj}}; born March 8, 1992), better known by his [[YouTube]] username '''VitalyzdTv''', is a Russian-American [[YouTube personality]] and pornographer<ref>{{cite web |title=Vitaly Uncensored |url=https://vitalyuncensored.com}}</ref>.\nZdorovetskiy's YouTube videos, as of November 2019, have reached over 1.7 billion views and over 10 million subscribers, while his [[vlog]] channel has more than 270 million views and 2.0 million subscribers.\n\n==Early life and education==\nZdorovetskiy was born in a Russian family in Murmansk in 1992. As a child, he lived in the Ukrainian city of Odessa. Zdorovetskiy grew up in [[Boca Raton, Florida]].\n\nZdorovetskiy attempted to become a professional skateboarder at an early age but gave up due to injuries.<ref name=Eng>{{cite web |url=http://upressonline.com/2013/02/faus-prank-star-vitaly-zdorovetskiy/ |title=FAU\u2019s Prank-Star: Vitaly Zdorovetskiy |author=Bryant Eng |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=February 5, 2013 |publisher=University Press Online}}</ref>\n\nIn the video titled \"Why I Did Porn!\", Zdorovetskiy tells his audience he got his first job at age 15 as a garbage collector making $5.00 an hour. His second job was a sign-spinner dressed as Uncle Sam making $20 for 3 hours of work. After that, Vitaly picked up a job as a bus boy at a restaurant in [[Miami|Miami, Florida]]. Shortly after turning 18, Zdorovetskiy took part in an [[pornographic film|adult film]] scene with [[pornography|pornographic]] actress Diamond Kitty for the adult entertainment company [[Bang Bros]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Eng\" />\n\n==Career==\nIn 2012, Zdorovetskiy received his first significant success, with the video \"Miami Zombie Attack Prank!\" Inspired by the [[Miami cannibal attack|cannibal attack of a homeless man in Miami]] in May 2012, Zdorovetskiy dressed up as a zombie and traveled to some of the poorest neighborhoods in Miami to scare random bystanders. By January 2015, the \"Miami Zombie Attack Prank!\" had been viewed more than 30 million times.<ref name=Eng /> A sequel video prank was produced in [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]], [[Ohio]]. The video got five million views within a week on YouTube.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2429039/The-moment-practical-joker-terrifies-Columbus-Ohio-residents-chasing-streets-wearing-hockey-mask-wielding-chainsaw.html |title=The moment practical joker terrifies Columbus, Ohio residents by chasing them in the streets wearing a hockey mask and wielding a chainsaw |newspaper=[[Mail Online]]|accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=September 22, 2013}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=September 2019}}\n\nOn June 16, 2012, Zdorovetskiy and cameraman Jonathan Vanegas filmed the \"Russian Hitman Prank\". As part of the prank, Zdorovetskiy approached a [[Boca Raton Resort]] man and informed him they had 60 seconds to get away from a briefcase he placed on the ground. After Zdorovetskiy revealed the whole thing to be a prank and that there was a [[hidden camera]] nearby, the man started attacking him and his partner and called the police. Zdorovetskiy was arrested by Boca Raton police department, facing a maximum of 15 years in prison<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/region_s_palm_beach_county/boca_raton/miami-zombie-attack-prankster-jonathan-vanegas-arrested-after-prank-goes-wrong-man-fights-back |title='Miami Zombie Attack' pranksters Jonathan Vanegas, Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested after prank fails |last1=Clarkson |first1=Brett |last2=Komenda |first2=Ed |last3=Sentinel |first3=Sun |date=July 17, 2012 |publisher=wptv.com |accessdate=February 21, 2013}}</ref> on charges of threatening to detonate a bomb. At the time of the prank, Zdorovetskiy's YouTube channel had only about 100,000 subscribers, but after the incident his channel grew to over four million subscribers within just over a year.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailydot.com/news/youtube-prank-vitaly-zdorovetskiy-bomb-threat/ |title=YouTube Rascal Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested for bomb hoax |work=[[Daily Dot]] |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |author=Chase Hoffberger |date=June 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn July 20, 2013, Zdorovetskiy released the video \"Extreme Homeless Man Makeover\", in which he befriends a homeless man named Martin and provides him with new clothes and a hotel room. The video posting resulted in a job offer that Martin accepted.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thedp.com/article/2013/12/youtube-pranksters-gone-good |title=Youtube pranksters gone good |author=Jeff Nadel |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=December 8, 2013 |newspaper=[[The Daily Pennsylvanian]]}}</ref> He was also reunited with his wife. The project also included an attempt to raise money to have Martin's teeth fixed, for which Zdorovetskiy was able to raise about $10,000 online. The fundraising campaign was canceled before it was completed, because of Zdorovetskiy's criminal history. However, Zdorovetskiy received several offers from surgeons to do the dental work for free.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.browardpalmbeach.com/pulp/2013/08/vitaly_zdorovetskiy_martin_homeless_indiegogo.php |publisher=Palm Beach New Times |title=Indiegogo Closes Vitaly Zdorovetskiy's Campaign To Fix Homeless Guy's Teeth |author=Terrence McCoy |date=August 13, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014}}</ref> The surgery and the video story was featured on television news casts including the ''Good Day LA'' Fox morning show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.myfoxla.com/story/23893739/vitaly-the-extreme-homeless-makeover |title=Vitaly: The Extreme Homeless Makeover |date=November 6, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |author=Jeffrey Thomas DeSocio |publisher=[[KTTV-TV|Fox 11]]}}</ref>\n\nHis \"Gold Digger Prank\", featuring a woman who rejects his advances until she believes he drives a [[Lamborghini Gallardo]] sports car,<ref>{{cite web |title=Viral \u2018Gold Digger Prank\u2019 Shows Woman Reject Guy For Date\u2026Until She Sees He Drives a Lamborghini or other expensive cars |url=http://www.theblaze.com/stories/2013/10/15/viral-gold-digger-prank-shows-woman-reject-guy-for-date-until-she-sees-he-drives-a-lamborghini/ |date=October 15, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |publisher=The Blaze}}</ref> generated more than 18 million views in its first week of posting,<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.adweek.com/videowatch/gold-digger-prank-nabs-18-million-youtube-views-week-153298 |title=Gold Digger Prank Nabs 18 Million YouTube Views in a Week Motorboarding for breast cancer, Aquaman round out VideoWatch ranker |author=Mike Shields |date=October 22, 2013 |accessdate=January 6, 2014 |magazine=[[Adweek]]}}</ref> making VitalyzdTV the third most watched YouTube channel in the world during that week with over 45 million views.<ref name=TF>{{cite web |url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2013/10/26/most-viewed-youtube-channels-worldwide-102513/ |title=Top 50 Most Viewed YouTube Channels Worldwide \u2013 Week Of 10/25/13 |author=Joshua Cohen |date=October 26, 2013 |accessdate=January 6, 2014 |publisher=TubeFilter}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he was arrested for invading the field during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup Final]] between [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|last1=White|first1=Ted|title=Youtube celebrity kicked out of Boca Raton Resort and Club, hours after checking in|url=http://www.wpbf.com/article/youtube-star-kicked-out-of-boca-resort/14754435|accessdate=January 16, 2018|work=WPBF|date=January 4, 2018|location=Boca Raton}}</ref>\n \nOn October 15, 2014, Zdorovetskiy pulled a prank which involved himself dressing up as Leatherface from ''[[The Texas Chain Saw Massacre]]'', pretending to saw off the legs of [[Hanhart syndrome]] patient Nick Santonastasso with a chainsaw in front of unsuspecting witnesses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/news/zombie-prankster-high-school-wrestler-nj-teen-inspires-despite-disability-2D12008775|title='Dead' man living: Disabled teen-turned-Internet star 'lives by inspiring others'|author=Scott Stump|work=TODAY.com}}</ref> The prank went viral, receiving over 30 million views in 3 weeks.\n\nOn May 25, 2016, Zdorovetskiy was arrested for trespassing after climbing the [[Hollywood Sign]], as part of a video stunt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/youtube-prankster-climbs-hollywood-sign-takes-selfies-for-movie-stunt-1201783386/|title=YouTube Star Arrested After Climbing Hollywood Sign|date=2016-05-26|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2016-05-26}}</ref> On June 10, Zdorovetskiy was again arrested for streaking during Game 4 of the [[2016 NBA Finals|NBA Finals]] between the [[Cleveland Cavaliers]] and the [[Golden State Warriors]] with authorities quickly apprehending and arresting the YouTuber.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.opencourt-basketball.com/youtuber-vitalyzdtv-streaks-2016-nba-finals/|title=Youtuber VitalyZDTV Streaks 2016 NBA Finals|date=2016-06-11|website=Opencourt Basketball|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-12}}</ref>\n\nDuring the bottom of the 7th inning in Game 5 of the [[2017 World Series]], he was arrested for running onto the field at [[Minute Maid Park]] shortly after [[Carlos Correa]] of the [[Houston Astros]] hit a home run.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/baseball/shirtless-fan-runs-field-game-5-world-series-article-1.3599082|title=Shirtless fan runs onto the field in Game 5 of the World Series - NY Daily News|date=October 30, 2017|website=NY Daily News|access-date=January 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn December 31, 2017, Zdorovetskiy and his girlfriend were escorted off Boca Raton Resort because online posts were discovered about a potential New Year's Eve prank, but Zdorovetskiy said he had no intention of making any prank videos at the resort. During the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]], his girlfriend Kinsey Wolanski [[Pitch invasion|ran on to the pitch]] wearing a swimsuit emblazoned with the \"Vitaly Uncensored\" logo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/sport/460843-kinsey-wolanski-pitch-invader/|title=Kinsey Wolanski: The blonde behind the Champions League pitch invasion (PHOTOS)|publisher=RT.com}}</ref> Zdorovetskiy is currently facing a ban from attending major sporting events for his antics and Wolanski is likely to get a similar ban. However, during the [[2019 Cricket World Cup Final]] between [[England national cricket team|England]] and [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealand]], Zdorovetskiy's mother, Elena Vulitsky attempted to emulate her son's girlfriend's success at the Champions League final.<ref>{{cite web |title=World Cup 2019: Streaker attempts pitch invasion in ENG vs NZ final|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket-world-cup/world-cup-final-2019-streaker-attempts-pitch-invasion-in-eng-vs-nz-5829041|accessdate=July 15, 2019|work=Indian Express|date=July 14, 2019|location=Guwahati}}</ref> Vulitsky was pictured wearing clothing with the \"Vitaly Uncensored\" logo on it, but was stopped by stewards from streaking.\n\nIn January 2020, Zdorovetskiy was arrested and spent five days in an Egyptian jail after climbing the [[Giza pyramid complex|Pyramids of Giza]].<ref>{{cite web | title=YouTuber's five days of hell in Egypt prison after climbing pyramids to take selfies|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/youtubers-five-days-hell-egypt-21297727|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, 2020, Zdorovetskiy was arrested for allegedly randomly assaulting a female jogger in Miami Beach. Reportedly, he jumped out of his car and attacked her, straddling her while punching her in the chest and face. The attack required her to get stitches for a cut. She reportedly told police she never met or knew who he was. He was later found hiding in a nearby house by Miami Beach police and charged with felony aggravated battery. He was released from custody after posting a $7,500 bond.<ref>{{cite web | title=YouTube star Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested for attacking female jogger|url=https://nypost.com/2020/04/14/youtube-star-vitaly-zdorovetskiy-arrested-for-attacking-jogger/|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=YouTube prankster arrested after attack on Miami Beach jogger, TMZ reports|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/local/miami-dade/fl-ne-youtube-prankster-vitaly-miami-beach-20200414-lt7igfrteffnpjln5wsfo2smrm-story.html|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nZdorovetskiy currently lives in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]]. He is in a movie with his friends [[Roman Atwood]] and [[Dennis Roady]], both fellow YouTube pranksters. In November 2015, Lionsgate officially acquired worldwide distribution rights for ''[[Natural Born Pranksters]].''<ref>{{Cite web|title = Lionsgate Picks Up Movie About YouTube Pranksters|url = http://time.com/4102845/lionsgate-youtube-pranksters-movie/|website = TIME.com|accessdate = 2015-12-27|first = Olivia B.|last = Waxman}}</ref> Upon debut, ''Natural Born Pranksters'' received poor reviews from viewers with an average user rating of 3.6 out of 10 on [[IMDb]],<ref name=\"IMDb\">{{cite web |title=Natural Born Pranksters (2016) - IMDb |url=https://m.imdb.com/title/tt3671086/ |website=IMDB.com |publisher=IMDb |accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref> and a 3.3 out of 10 on [[Metacritic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Natural Born Pranksters Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/natural-born-pranksters |website=Metacritic.com |publisher=Metacritic |accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/VitalyzdTv Official YouTube channel]\n* {{IMDb name|6014413}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zdorovetskiy, Vitaly}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian male comedians]]\n[[Category:Pranksters]]\n[[Category:People from Murmansk]]\n[[Category:Russian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Russian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Streakers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriates in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name            = Vitaly Zdorovetskiy\n| image           = \n| caption         = \n| channel_name    = VitalyzdTv\n| views           = 1.69+ billion\n| view_date =January 24, 2020\n| birth_name      = \n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1992|03|08}}\n| birth_place     = [[Murmansk]], [[Murmansk Oblast]], [[Russian Federation]]\n| origin          = [[Boca Raton, Florida]], United States| Current Residence         = [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n| nationality     = Russian \n| alma_mater      = Boca Raton Community High School\n| occupation      = YouTube personality, actor, businessman\n| website         = \n| pseudonym       = \n| years_active    = 2011\u2013present\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Practical joke|Pranking]]\n* [[comedy]]\n}}\n| subscribers     = 10.3+ million \n| subscriber_date = January 9, 2020\n| network         = [[Disney Digital Network|Maker]] (2011\u20132014)<br />[[Collective Digital Studio|Collective Digital]] (2014\u2013present)\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* [[Roman Atwood]]\n* [[Dennis Roady]]\n* [[Yousef Erakat]]\n* [[Protosun Productions]]\n* [[Nelk Boys]]\n* [[Logan Paul]]\n}}\n| silver_button   = yes\n| silver_year     = 2012\n| gold_button     = yes\n| gold_year       = 2013\n| diamond_button     = yes\n| diamond_year       = 2019\n| stats_update    = November 19, 2019\n}}\n\n'''Vitaly Zdorovetskiy''' ({{IPAc-en|v|\u026a|\u02c8|t|\u00e6|l|i|_|z|\u0259|\u02cc|d|\u0252r|\u0259|\u02c8|v|j|\u025b|t|s|k|i}} {{respell|vih|TAL|ee|_|z\u0259|DORR|\u0259|VYET|skee}}; {{lang-rus|link=no|\u0412\u0438\u0442\u0430\u0301\u043b\u0438\u0439 \u0417\u0434\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0435\u0301\u0446\u043a\u0438\u0439|p=v\u02b2\u026a\u02c8tal\u02b2\u026aj zd\u0259r\u0250\u02c8v\u02b2\u025btsk\u02b2\u026aj}}; born March 8, 1992), better known by his [[YouTube]] username '''VitalyzdTv''', is a Russian-American [[YouTube personality]] and pornographer<ref>{{cite web |title=Vitaly Uncensored |url=https://vitalyuncensored.com}}</ref>.\nZdorovetskiy's YouTube videos, as of November 2019, have reached over 1.7 billion views and over 10 million subscribers, while his [[vlog]] channel has more than 270 million views and 2.0 million subscribers.\n\n==Early life and education==\nZdorovetskiy was born in a Russian family in Murmansk in 1992. As a child, he lived in the Ukrainian city of Odessa. Zdorovetskiy grew up in [[Boca Raton, Florida]].\n\nZdorovetskiy attempted to become a professional skateboarder at an early age but gave up due to injuries.<ref name=Eng>{{cite web |url=http://upressonline.com/2013/02/faus-prank-star-vitaly-zdorovetskiy/ |title=FAU\u2019s Prank-Star: Vitaly Zdorovetskiy |author=Bryant Eng |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=February 5, 2013 |publisher=University Press Online}}</ref>\n\nIn the video titled \"Why I Did Porn!\", Zdorovetskiy tells his audience he got his first job at age 15 as a garbage collector making $5.00 an hour. His second job was a sign-spinner dressed as Uncle Sam making $20 for 3 hours of work. After that, Vitaly picked up a job as a bus boy at a restaurant in [[Miami|Miami, Florida]]. Shortly after turning 18, Zdorovetskiy took part in an [[pornographic film|adult film]] scene with [[pornography|pornographic]] actress Diamond Kitty for the adult entertainment company [[Bang Bros]] in 2011.<ref name=\"Eng\" />\n\n==Career==\nIn 2012, Zdorovetskiy received his first significant success, with the video \"Miami Zombie Attack Prank!\" Inspired by the [[Miami cannibal attack|cannibal attack of a homeless man in Miami]] in May 2012, Zdorovetskiy dressed up as a zombie and traveled to some of the poorest neighborhoods in Miami to scare random bystanders. By January 2015, the \"Miami Zombie Attack Prank!\" had been viewed more than 30 million times.<ref name=Eng /> A sequel video prank was produced in [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]], [[Ohio]]. The video got five million views within a week on YouTube.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2429039/The-moment-practical-joker-terrifies-Columbus-Ohio-residents-chasing-streets-wearing-hockey-mask-wielding-chainsaw.html |title=The moment practical joker terrifies Columbus, Ohio residents by chasing them in the streets wearing a hockey mask and wielding a chainsaw |newspaper=[[Mail Online]]|accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=September 22, 2013}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=September 2019}}\n\nOn June 16, 2012, Zdorovetskiy and cameraman Jonathan Vanegas filmed the \"Russian Hitman Prank\". As part of the prank, Zdorovetskiy approached a [[Boca Raton Resort]] man and informed him they had 60 seconds to get away from a briefcase he placed on the ground. After Zdorovetskiy revealed the whole thing to be a prank and that there was a [[hidden camera]] nearby, the man started attacking him and his partner and called the police. Zdorovetskiy was arrested by Boca Raton police department, facing a maximum of 15 years in prison<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wptv.com/dpp/news/region_s_palm_beach_county/boca_raton/miami-zombie-attack-prankster-jonathan-vanegas-arrested-after-prank-goes-wrong-man-fights-back |title='Miami Zombie Attack' pranksters Jonathan Vanegas, Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested after prank fails |last1=Clarkson |first1=Brett |last2=Komenda |first2=Ed |last3=Sentinel |first3=Sun |date=July 17, 2012 |publisher=wptv.com |accessdate=February 21, 2013}}</ref> on charges of threatening to detonate a bomb. At the time of the prank, Zdorovetskiy's YouTube channel had only about 100,000 subscribers, but after the incident his channel grew to over four million subscribers within just over a year.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailydot.com/news/youtube-prank-vitaly-zdorovetskiy-bomb-threat/ |title=YouTube Rascal Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested for bomb hoax |work=[[Daily Dot]] |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |author=Chase Hoffberger |date=June 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn July 20, 2013, Zdorovetskiy released the video \"Extreme Homeless Man Makeover\", in which he befriends a homeless man named Martin and provides him with new clothes and a hotel room. The video posting resulted in a job offer that Martin accepted.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thedp.com/article/2013/12/youtube-pranksters-gone-good |title=Youtube pranksters gone good |author=Jeff Nadel |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |date=December 8, 2013 |newspaper=[[The Daily Pennsylvanian]]}}</ref> He was also reunited with his wife. The project also included an attempt to raise money to have Martin's teeth fixed, for which Zdorovetskiy was able to raise about $10,000 online. The fundraising campaign was canceled before it was completed, because of Zdorovetskiy's criminal history. However, Zdorovetskiy received several offers from surgeons to do the dental work for free.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.browardpalmbeach.com/pulp/2013/08/vitaly_zdorovetskiy_martin_homeless_indiegogo.php |publisher=Palm Beach New Times |title=Indiegogo Closes Vitaly Zdorovetskiy's Campaign To Fix Homeless Guy's Teeth |author=Terrence McCoy |date=August 13, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014}}</ref> The surgery and the video story was featured on television news casts including the ''Good Day LA'' Fox morning show.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.myfoxla.com/story/23893739/vitaly-the-extreme-homeless-makeover |title=Vitaly: The Extreme Homeless Makeover |date=November 6, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |author=Jeffrey Thomas DeSocio |publisher=[[KTTV-TV|Fox 11]]}}</ref>\n\nHis \"Gold Digger Prank\", featuring a woman who rejects his advances until she believes he drives a [[Lamborghini Gallardo]] sports car,<ref>{{cite web |title=Viral \u2018Gold Digger Prank\u2019 Shows Woman Reject Guy For Date\u2026Until She Sees He Drives a Lamborghini or other expensive cars |url=http://www.theblaze.com/stories/2013/10/15/viral-gold-digger-prank-shows-woman-reject-guy-for-date-until-she-sees-he-drives-a-lamborghini/ |date=October 15, 2013 |accessdate=January 2, 2014 |publisher=The Blaze}}</ref> generated more than 18 million views in its first week of posting,<ref>{{cite magazine |url=http://www.adweek.com/videowatch/gold-digger-prank-nabs-18-million-youtube-views-week-153298 |title=Gold Digger Prank Nabs 18 Million YouTube Views in a Week Motorboarding for breast cancer, Aquaman round out VideoWatch ranker |author=Mike Shields |date=October 22, 2013 |accessdate=January 6, 2014 |magazine=[[Adweek]]}}</ref> making VitalyzdTV the third most watched YouTube channel in the world during that week with over 45 million views.<ref name=TF>{{cite web |url=http://www.tubefilter.com/2013/10/26/most-viewed-youtube-channels-worldwide-102513/ |title=Top 50 Most Viewed YouTube Channels Worldwide \u2013 Week Of 10/25/13 |author=Joshua Cohen |date=October 26, 2013 |accessdate=January 6, 2014 |publisher=TubeFilter}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he was arrested for invading the field during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup Final]] between [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] in Brazil.<ref>{{cite news|last1=White|first1=Ted|title=Youtube celebrity kicked out of Boca Raton Resort and Club, hours after checking in|url=http://www.wpbf.com/article/youtube-star-kicked-out-of-boca-resort/14754435|accessdate=January 16, 2018|work=WPBF|date=January 4, 2018|location=Boca Raton}}</ref>\n \nOn October 15, 2014, Zdorovetskiy pulled a prank which involved himself dressing up as Leatherface from ''[[The Texas Chain Saw Massacre]]'', pretending to saw off the legs of [[Hanhart syndrome]] patient Nick Santonastasso with a chainsaw in front of unsuspecting witnesses.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.today.com/news/zombie-prankster-high-school-wrestler-nj-teen-inspires-despite-disability-2D12008775|title='Dead' man living: Disabled teen-turned-Internet star 'lives by inspiring others'|author=Scott Stump|work=TODAY.com}}</ref> The prank went viral, receiving over 30 million views in 3 weeks.\n\nOn May 25, 2016, Zdorovetskiy was arrested for trespassing after climbing the [[Hollywood Sign]], as part of a video stunt.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/youtube-prankster-climbs-hollywood-sign-takes-selfies-for-movie-stunt-1201783386/|title=YouTube Star Arrested After Climbing Hollywood Sign|date=2016-05-26|website=Variety|language=en-US|access-date=2016-05-26}}</ref> On June 10, Zdorovetskiy was again arrested for streaking during Game 4 of the [[2016 NBA Finals|NBA Finals]] between the [[Cleveland Cavaliers]] and the [[Golden State Warriors]] with authorities quickly apprehending and arresting the YouTuber.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.opencourt-basketball.com/youtuber-vitalyzdtv-streaks-2016-nba-finals/|title=Youtuber VitalyZDTV Streaks 2016 NBA Finals|date=2016-06-11|website=Opencourt Basketball|language=en-US|access-date=2016-06-12}}</ref>\n\nDuring the bottom of the 7th inning in Game 5 of the [[2017 World Series]], he was arrested for running onto the field at [[Minute Maid Park]] shortly after [[Carlos Correa]] of the [[Houston Astros]] hit a home run.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/sports/baseball/shirtless-fan-runs-field-game-5-world-series-article-1.3599082|title=Shirtless fan runs onto the field in Game 5 of the World Series - NY Daily News|date=October 30, 2017|website=NY Daily News|access-date=January 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn December 31, 2017, Zdorovetskiy and his girlfriend were escorted off Boca Raton Resort because online posts were discovered about a potential New Year's Eve prank, but Zdorovetskiy said he had no intention of making any prank videos at the resort. During the [[2019 UEFA Champions League Final]], his girlfriend Kinsey Wolanski [[Pitch invasion|ran on to the pitch]] wearing a swimsuit emblazoned with the \"Vitaly Uncensored\" logo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rt.com/sport/460843-kinsey-wolanski-pitch-invader/|title=Kinsey Wolanski: The blonde behind the Champions League pitch invasion (PHOTOS)|publisher=RT.com}}</ref> Zdorovetskiy is currently facing a ban from attending major sporting events for his antics and Wolanski is likely to get a similar ban. However, during the [[2019 Cricket World Cup Final]] between [[England national cricket team|England]] and [[New Zealand national cricket team|New Zealand]], Zdorovetskiy's mother, Elena Vulitsky attempted to emulate her son's girlfriend's success at the Champions League final.<ref>{{cite web |title=World Cup 2019: Streaker attempts pitch invasion in ENG vs NZ final|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/sports/cricket-world-cup/world-cup-final-2019-streaker-attempts-pitch-invasion-in-eng-vs-nz-5829041|accessdate=July 15, 2019|work=Indian Express|date=July 14, 2019|location=Guwahati}}</ref> Vulitsky was pictured wearing clothing with the \"Vitaly Uncensored\" logo on it, but was stopped by stewards from streaking.\n\nIn January 2020, Zdorovetskiy was arrested and spent five days in an Egyptian jail after climbing the [[Giza pyramid complex|Pyramids of Giza]].<ref>{{cite web | title=YouTuber's five days of hell in Egypt prison after climbing pyramids to take selfies|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/youtubers-five-days-hell-egypt-21297727|accessdate=January 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn April 12, 2020, Zdorovetskiy was arrested for allegedly randomly assaulting a female jogger in Miami Beach. Reportedly, he jumped out of his car and attacked her, straddling her while punching her in the chest and face. The attack required her to get stitches for a cut. She reportedly told police she never met or knew who he was. He was later found hiding in a nearby house by Miami Beach police and charged with felony aggravated battery. He was released from custody after posting a $7,500 bond.<ref>{{cite web | title=YouTube star Vitaly Zdorovetskiy arrested for attacking female jogger|url=https://nypost.com/2020/04/14/youtube-star-vitaly-zdorovetskiy-arrested-for-attacking-jogger/|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title=YouTube prankster arrested after attack on Miami Beach jogger, TMZ reports|url=https://www.sun-sentinel.com/local/miami-dade/fl-ne-youtube-prankster-vitaly-miami-beach-20200414-lt7igfrteffnpjln5wsfo2smrm-story.html|accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nZdorovetskiy currently lives in [[Los Angeles|Los Angeles, California]]. He is in a movie with his friends [[Roman Atwood]] and [[Dennis Roady]], both fellow YouTube pranksters. In November 2015, Lionsgate officially acquired worldwide distribution rights for ''[[Natural Born Pranksters]].''<ref>{{Cite web|title = Lionsgate Picks Up Movie About YouTube Pranksters|url = http://time.com/4102845/lionsgate-youtube-pranksters-movie/|website = TIME.com|accessdate = 2015-12-27|first = Olivia B.|last = Waxman}}</ref> Upon debut, ''Natural Born Pranksters'' received poor reviews from viewers with an average user rating of 3.6 out of 10 on [[IMDb]],<ref name=\"IMDb\">{{cite web |title=Natural Born Pranksters (2016) - IMDb |url=https://m.imdb.com/title/tt3671086/ |website=IMDB.com |publisher=IMDb |accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref> and a 3.3 out of 10 on [[Metacritic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Natural Born Pranksters Reviews |url=https://www.metacritic.com/movie/natural-born-pranksters |website=Metacritic.com |publisher=Metacritic |accessdate=3 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/user/VitalyzdTv Official YouTube channel]\n* {{IMDb name|6014413}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zdorovetskiy, Vitaly}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Russian male comedians]]\n[[Category:Pranksters]]\n[[Category:People from Murmansk]]\n[[Category:Russian emigrants to the United States]]\n[[Category:Russian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Streakers]]\n[[Category:Male YouTubers]]\n[[Category:American YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Russian expatriates in the United States]]\n", "name_user": "ZdorovetskiyVitaly", "label": "safe", "comment": "Include